Introduction: - PM SHRI (PM Schools for Rising India), a centrally sponsored scheme, is being implemented in the state since the year 2022-23. The expenditure on the scheme is borne by the Central Government and the State Government in the ratio 60:40 respectively. Reference No. The Central Government, by order 1B2, has issued a notification for this component of the Scheduled Castes Sub-Plan.

The second instalment of this current financial year has been deposited in the Consolidated Fund of the State. The proposal for devolution of this fund and its corresponding State share is referred to Reference No. Section 3 has been submitted to the government.
A proposal to approve it was under consideration of the government.
